WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:03.921
Hey.

00:03.921 --> 00:06.465
"We need to talk."

00:06.465 --> 00:08.884
Come in.
So, what's going on, man?

00:08.884 --> 00:11.887
What brings you here?

00:11.887 --> 00:13.805
Right.
In fairness,

00:13.805 --> 00:17.267
I do that a lot less
than when we started.

00:17.267 --> 00:18.227
Let's get you up there.

00:18.227 --> 00:19.478
[ Grunts ]

00:19.478 --> 00:20.938
[ Panting ]
Whew!

00:20.938 --> 00:21.980
How much do you weigh?

00:21.980 --> 00:23.148
No more chicken fingers.

00:23.148 --> 00:25.943
[ Grunts ]

00:25.943 --> 00:28.612
What?
Yes! I had garlic.

00:28.612 --> 00:31.531
You don't like it?
Don't kiss me.

00:31.531 --> 00:33.325
All right.

00:33.325 --> 00:34.910
Now the easy part.

00:34.910 --> 00:36.411
[ Yells ]

00:36.411 --> 00:38.455
[ Grunts ]

00:38.914 --> 00:39.873
[ Drill whirring ]

00:39.873 --> 00:41.542
[ Grunting ]

00:41.542 --> 00:43.126
Don't worry, JJ.

00:43.126 --> 00:44.795
It's not as hard
as it looks.

00:44.795 --> 00:46.547
[ Grunts ]

00:46.547 --> 00:48.298
Get back up there!

00:48.298 --> 00:52.094
Move another day!

00:52.094 --> 00:53.262
All right.

00:53.262 --> 00:55.764
Finally.

00:55.764 --> 00:57.391
Ah, come on, man!

00:57.391 --> 00:58.600
No!

00:58.600 --> 01:01.895
[ Panting ]

01:01.895 --> 01:03.188
Oh!

01:03.188 --> 01:04.773
Okay, buddy.
What do you need to say?

01:04.773 --> 01:09.194
"I want to live here."

01:09.194 --> 01:10.279
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:10.279 --> 01:12.197
I can't see
why that would be a problem.

01:12.197 --> 01:13.073
[ Sighs ]

01:17.077 --> 01:19.288
"My mom went from

01:19.288 --> 01:21.540
'You can do anything'

01:21.540 --> 01:24.334
to 'Who's going
to take JJ?' ‐‐

01:24.334 --> 01:27.921
Deciding my..."
F ‐‐

01:27.921 --> 01:30.966
"future
without me there."

01:34.928 --> 01:37.556
"Are we going to talk about

01:37.556 --> 01:41.977
that picture of you
with a mohawk?"

01:46.273 --> 01:48.233
We are not.

01:48.233 --> 01:49.401
I don't know, man.

01:49.401 --> 01:51.653
Running away...

01:51.653 --> 01:53.238
JJ, you know I love you.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.115
You know I'm looking out
for you ‐‐

01:55.115 --> 01:56.491
always.

01:56.491 --> 01:58.785
But I got to ‐‐
Damn!

01:58.785 --> 02:03.582
What wheelchair‐hating monster
designed this place?

02:03.582 --> 02:06.918
JJ, I can't let you do it.

02:06.918 --> 02:09.671
I got to take you back.

02:09.671 --> 02:12.549
I'm sorry, buddy.

02:12.549 --> 02:14.092
Ow!

02:14.092 --> 02:15.594
See?

02:15.594 --> 02:17.638
We were so scared
of this conversation.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.306
It's really
not that unpleasant.

02:19.306 --> 02:20.807
We're going to die.

02:20.807 --> 02:22.142
And you're going to die.

02:22.142 --> 02:24.978
JJ will die,
but until then,

02:24.978 --> 02:27.064
the not‐dead one of you
will be there,

02:27.064 --> 02:28.273
or, after that,
your children.

02:28.273 --> 02:30.484
Who will also die.

02:30.484 --> 02:31.735
Okay.

02:31.735 --> 02:33.362
Fun. Good.

02:33.362 --> 02:35.364
[ Cellphone rings ]

02:35.364 --> 02:36.406
All right.

02:36.406 --> 02:38.033
Dad, can I ask you
one other thing

02:38.033 --> 02:41.286
about all this JJ stuff?

02:41.286 --> 02:42.537
Uh, oh, oh...

02:42.537 --> 02:43.705
Oh, hey!

02:43.705 --> 02:44.873
You know
what I just remembered?

02:44.873 --> 02:46.708
Haven't you guys
been bugging me for a while

02:46.708 --> 02:48.335
to go out for steak?

02:48.335 --> 02:50.921
Yes,
with my own baked potato.

02:50.921 --> 02:53.173
None of that
"family potato" noise.

02:53.173 --> 02:55.217
Call that fancy steakhouse
in town.

02:55.217 --> 02:56.635
Tell them we're coming.

02:56.635 --> 03:00.097
But, Dad,
we just ate dinner.

03:00.097 --> 03:01.306
[ Growls ]
No ‐‐ Okay.
Go to the car.

03:01.306 --> 03:02.599
Go to the car.
Daddy's gonna feed you.

03:02.599 --> 03:03.517
Daddy's gonna feed you.

03:03.517 --> 03:05.435
JJ was here? He heard us?

03:05.435 --> 03:08.188
He did. It was a real
saloon door to the face.

03:08.188 --> 03:09.648
What?
20 years in this country,

03:09.648 --> 03:11.775
and I still don't understand
your colorful expressions.

03:11.775 --> 03:13.527
<i>Poor JJ. How is he?</i>

03:13.527 --> 03:16.238
I'm bringing him home,
but he's upset,

03:16.238 --> 03:18.198
so just hear him out.

03:18.198 --> 03:19.908
<i>Don't do anything weird</i>
<i>or cute.</i>

03:19.908 --> 03:22.619
Don't DiMeo this up.

03:22.619 --> 03:24.746
Darling, I'm so sorry.

03:24.746 --> 03:27.416
Anything we said,
we said with love and respect.

03:27.416 --> 03:28.750
But still, it was wrong.

03:28.750 --> 03:30.877
We shouldn't have had
any talk about your future

03:30.877 --> 03:31.753
without you there ‐‐

03:31.753 --> 03:34.172
period.

03:34.172 --> 03:35.966
So we shall pay.

03:35.966 --> 03:37.259
♪♪

03:37.259 --> 03:38.969
The Carolina reaper
pepper ‐‐

03:38.969 --> 03:40.971
hottest pepper
known to man ‐‐

03:40.971 --> 03:44.474
2.2 million Scoville units.

03:44.474 --> 03:47.686
The jalapeño, by comparison,
has only 2,500.

03:47.686 --> 03:51.606
We have hurt you,
and now it is our turn to hurt.

03:51.606 --> 03:53.817
One, two...

03:53.817 --> 03:55.318
You DiMeo'd it.

03:55.318 --> 03:57.737
Ah, thank God.

03:57.737 --> 03:58.697
For a second there,

03:58.697 --> 04:01.074
I actually thought
we were gonna ‐‐

04:01.074 --> 04:03.910
[ Screams ]

04:03.910 --> 04:06.204
It's in my eyes!
End this!

04:06.204 --> 04:08.165
Get a gun
and shoot me in the face!

04:08.165 --> 04:09.374
[ Screams ]

04:09.374 --> 04:12.544
We just wanted to show you
how sorry we all feel.

04:12.544 --> 04:14.379
"You" S‐H‐‐ "should."

04:14.379 --> 04:15.672
"Mom, you said" ‐‐

04:15.672 --> 04:17.090
Oh, he's yelling at me.

04:17.090 --> 04:18.467
Someone else read it ‐‐
can't yell at myself.

04:18.467 --> 04:20.343
On it.

04:20.343 --> 04:23.889
"Mom said I couldn't live
on my own,

04:23.889 --> 04:26.016
and, Dad,
you didn't think to" ‐‐

04:26.016 --> 04:28.769
He's yelling at me.
Dylan!

04:28.769 --> 04:29.936
Ray, hurry.

04:29.936 --> 04:32.189
I'm gonna yell for JJ,
but you're next.

04:32.189 --> 04:33.607
Ray: Is there an ETA
on that gun?

04:33.607 --> 04:37.027
"You think I'm a"
B‐U‐‐ "burden."

04:37.027 --> 04:40.489
"A" H‐O‐‐ "Hot potato
to pass around."

04:40.489 --> 04:42.699
See?
I told you he was mad.

04:42.699 --> 04:45.827
"I'm mad at you, too."

04:45.827 --> 04:47.496
Me?!

04:47.496 --> 04:49.664
"You brought me home."

04:49.664 --> 04:51.708
Because your problems can't
be solved by running away.

04:51.708 --> 04:53.502
You were running away? That's
why you were at Kenneth's?

04:53.502 --> 04:55.295
Uh‐huh.
Oh, and you just
brought him back

04:55.295 --> 04:57.297
like he was some bull that
went over the neighbor's fence?

04:57.297 --> 04:59.508
You don't think JJ
has a right to run away?

04:59.508 --> 05:00.884
What is this?

05:00.884 --> 05:02.761
He has the same rights
as anybody else.

05:02.761 --> 05:05.847
If he were any other teen,
he'd be halfway to Provo by now.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.432
Provo?
Runaway capital
of the world.

05:07.432 --> 05:08.850
You wanted to run away?

05:08.850 --> 05:10.519
Do you still
want to run away?

05:10.519 --> 05:12.103
Then the fact
that you use a wheelchair

05:12.103 --> 05:14.731
should not stop you
from getting what you want.

05:14.731 --> 05:16.274
Let's get you packed, JJ.

05:16.274 --> 05:18.109
I'm running you away ‐‐

05:18.109 --> 05:19.945
from me.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.488
Can you drop me off
at the hospital first?

05:25.116 --> 05:26.368
Wow.

05:26.368 --> 05:28.161
Mom and JJ
are still going at it.

05:28.161 --> 05:30.080
Did you notice
anything odd

05:30.080 --> 05:31.706
about the whole
"fancy steakhouse" thing?

05:31.706 --> 05:33.750
Yeah.
You ordered the chicken.

05:33.750 --> 05:34.584
What is wrong with you?

05:34.584 --> 05:35.836
No.

05:35.836 --> 05:37.671
The whole thing
was a diversion.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.339
Dad got all weird
when Mom left

05:39.339 --> 05:40.632
and I asked about JJ.

05:40.632 --> 05:43.677
It's like emotional talks
short‐circuit his brain.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.136
You're right.

05:45.136 --> 05:47.180
Imagine all the stuff
we could get from him

05:47.180 --> 05:48.723
if we use this
against him.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.559
You don't think
he's too savvy for that?

05:50.559 --> 05:53.103
The man's e‐mail password
is the number four,

05:53.103 --> 05:54.813
and that's only because
we had to reset it for him

05:54.813 --> 05:56.273
three times.

05:56.273 --> 05:58.483
Right ‐‐ pants, socks, shirt,
got all of that.

05:58.483 --> 05:59.484
What else do we need?

05:59.484 --> 06:01.945
"To get a" G‐R‐‐ "grip."

06:01.945 --> 06:04.364
Now, where are we going,
and why are you running away?

06:04.364 --> 06:06.992
Is it adventure
or are you sending a message?

06:06.992 --> 06:09.828
"To see
what I can do alone."

06:09.828 --> 06:10.704
Well, you will be alone...

06:10.704 --> 06:12.330
with me.

06:12.330 --> 06:15.125
"You can't do
everything for me."

06:15.125 --> 06:16.543
Why? Why can't I?

06:16.543 --> 06:19.170
Nobody tells me what I can
and can't do for my son,

06:19.170 --> 06:21.047
even my son.

06:21.047 --> 06:24.175
"Fine, but we go
wherever <i>I</i> want."

06:24.175 --> 06:25.677
Yeah, well,
you don't scare me.

06:25.677 --> 06:28.597
"I'll need my"
S‐L‐‐ "sleeping bag,

06:28.597 --> 06:29.723
my passport" ‐‐

06:29.723 --> 06:31.683
Yeah, that's the spirit.
Done.

06:31.683 --> 06:33.184
"And money."

06:33.184 --> 06:34.519
You stole 40 bucks
from your mum ‐‐

06:34.519 --> 06:35.478
broke her heart.

06:35.478 --> 06:38.231
♪♪

06:38.231 --> 06:39.274
Hey, guys.

06:39.274 --> 06:40.567
Everything okay?

06:40.567 --> 06:42.152
Sounds like Mom and JJ
are talking

06:42.152 --> 06:44.070
about some
pretty <i>heavy</i> stuff.

06:44.070 --> 06:46.615
Yeah, I have
a bunch of...

06:46.615 --> 06:48.742
feelings and whatnot

06:48.742 --> 06:50.076
I‐I want to say.

06:50.076 --> 06:52.245
Okay. Sounds good.

06:52.245 --> 06:53.580
Or...
Liking this.

06:53.580 --> 06:56.625
...there is a new video game
we wanted to get.

06:56.625 --> 06:58.543
Take my card.

06:58.543 --> 07:00.629
If anyone asks, the password
is the number five.

07:00.629 --> 07:01.963
Can we drink soda
and sleep on the roof?

07:01.963 --> 07:03.506
Sure.
Can I swear?

07:03.506 --> 07:05.425
Which words.
[Bleep], [bleep],
and [bleep].

07:05.425 --> 07:06.426
Yes.

07:06.426 --> 07:07.469
What about [bleep]?

07:07.469 --> 07:09.846
Quietly.

07:09.846 --> 07:11.097
Good talk.

07:11.097 --> 07:12.766
Yeah.

07:12.766 --> 07:15.393
All right, time to say goodbye
to our little runaway.

07:15.393 --> 07:17.771
Listen, JJ, maybe I shouldn't
have rushed you home.

07:17.771 --> 07:19.981
I'm sorry.

07:19.981 --> 07:23.318
"Hey, Mom, Kenneth
used to be a" ‐‐

07:23.318 --> 07:25.070
No.

07:25.070 --> 07:27.697
[ Whispering ]
Stop it.

07:27.697 --> 07:29.991
"Kenneth used to be a flamboyant
college basketball star."

07:29.991 --> 07:32.827
Kenneth used to be a flamboyant
college basketball star?

07:32.827 --> 07:33.912
It's no big deal.

07:33.912 --> 07:34.788
Are you kidding?

07:34.788 --> 07:36.581
It's a huge [bleep] deal!

07:36.581 --> 07:38.249
Are we good with this?
We are.

07:38.249 --> 07:39.584
There's another winner
in this house?

07:39.584 --> 07:40.585
Not now.

07:40.585 --> 07:42.545
Yeah! Winners! Yeah.

07:42.545 --> 07:44.047
Full force.

07:44.047 --> 07:46.424
I usually have to cut it in half
for these guys.

07:46.424 --> 07:47.634
Punks.

07:49.344 --> 07:51.638
Maya: Still no idea
where you want to go, eh?

07:51.638 --> 07:56.059
Oh, well. If you see something,
ring me up here.

07:56.059 --> 07:57.686
Ah.
Ah, darling, darling ‐‐

07:57.686 --> 07:58.853
No, no.
No, this was a bad idea ‐‐

07:58.853 --> 08:01.314
bad idea.

08:01.314 --> 08:02.607
Casino?

08:02.607 --> 08:04.109
What? Ow!
You're gambling

08:04.109 --> 08:05.694
with both our lives already,
darling.

08:05.694 --> 08:07.445
Okay, okay.

08:07.445 --> 08:09.280
You were a winner.

08:09.280 --> 08:10.740
The basketball thing?

08:10.740 --> 08:12.200
[ Sighs ]
It was no big deal.

08:12.200 --> 08:14.119
You were one
of the highest‐rated forwards

08:14.119 --> 08:15.704
in the country.

08:15.704 --> 08:16.955
They called you
The Grim Leaper.

08:16.955 --> 08:18.915
You had a mohawk.

08:18.915 --> 08:21.292
Huh.
That was a fun photo shoot.

08:21.292 --> 08:23.294
Dario really let me play.

08:23.294 --> 08:25.213
No, no, no ‐‐
Don't go.

08:25.213 --> 08:27.090
Finally, another person

08:27.090 --> 08:29.384
who has the spirit
of a champion.

08:29.384 --> 08:31.928
I've been living
in Jabroni city over here.

08:31.928 --> 08:32.846
It's good to meet you...

08:32.846 --> 08:34.097
friend.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.143
Dylan, it's true.

08:38.143 --> 08:39.728
I was a champion.

08:39.728 --> 08:40.729
A Grim Leaper.

08:40.729 --> 08:42.897
I had fame, fans,

08:42.897 --> 08:45.066
a fondness for Fatboy Slim's
"Rockafeller Skank,"

08:45.066 --> 08:46.443
and you know what?

08:46.443 --> 08:48.570
I regret every second of it.

08:48.570 --> 08:50.572
Why?
Because of
what it made me ‐‐

08:50.572 --> 08:52.198
so full of myself.

08:52.198 --> 08:55.160
I took gifts
from the boosters ‐‐

08:55.160 --> 08:58.538
a car, cash,
Fatboy Slim CDs.

08:58.538 --> 09:02.167
I got busted for it,
got dropped from the team,

09:02.167 --> 09:03.626
had to sell the Corvette...

09:03.626 --> 09:05.045
I crashed.

09:05.045 --> 09:08.757
Hard.
And that's how
you became this?

09:08.757 --> 09:10.759
Girl, you were hugging me
six seconds ago.

09:10.759 --> 09:12.469
[ Game music plays ]

09:12.469 --> 09:14.054
This is the best!

09:14.054 --> 09:16.598
Dad hasn't said no
to a single thing yet.

09:16.598 --> 09:20.143
What's next?
I've got a flamboyant
college athlete to fix.

09:20.143 --> 09:22.103
Think you can keep the
gravy train going for a while?

09:22.103 --> 09:23.438
Choo‐choo, baby.

09:23.438 --> 09:26.566
Call me biscuits
'cause I want that gravy.

09:26.566 --> 09:27.776
No.

09:27.776 --> 09:31.196
♪♪

09:31.196 --> 09:32.822
I'm not gonna stop you.
You're the runaway.

09:32.822 --> 09:35.033
Excuse me ‐‐ no one under 18
on the casino floor.

09:35.033 --> 09:36.159
18?

09:36.159 --> 09:37.327
He's my husband.

09:37.327 --> 09:39.329
Yeah, he's 36.
I mean, would they let a child

09:39.329 --> 09:41.831
be the third most successful
dentist in St. Paul?

09:41.831 --> 09:43.750
Rude.

09:43.750 --> 09:45.668
"Why are we married?"

09:45.668 --> 09:46.878
Because we love each other.

09:51.508 --> 09:53.218
Hey, Dad.

09:53.218 --> 09:57.472
I feel like our conversation
about JJ got interrupted,

09:57.472 --> 09:59.265
and now he's run away,

09:59.265 --> 10:01.810
and I'm ready for our talk ‐‐

10:01.810 --> 10:04.062
our ‐‐ our <i>heavy</i> talk.

10:04.062 --> 10:05.355
How would you like
a lollipop?

10:05.355 --> 10:06.314
Not interested.

10:06.314 --> 10:08.858
Maybe there's something
you do want.

10:08.858 --> 10:10.819
There is.

10:10.819 --> 10:12.237
I want a robe.

10:14.572 --> 10:15.573
What?

10:15.573 --> 10:17.200
That's right.

10:17.200 --> 10:19.244
And you better deliver,
or else,

10:19.244 --> 10:20.286
I don't know
what to tell you, pal.

10:20.286 --> 10:23.248
It is gonna get
real heavy.

10:23.248 --> 10:26.626
So that's what you ‐‐
you want? A robe?

10:26.626 --> 10:28.044
Like a lady
in a lotion commercial?

10:28.044 --> 10:31.047
No, like a boy in repose.

10:31.047 --> 10:33.550
Do you want to be
a boy in repose?

10:33.550 --> 10:35.218
What kind of robe?
Like a kimono?

10:35.218 --> 10:36.386
[ Sighs ]
Just forget I asked.

10:36.386 --> 10:37.762
What did he do?

10:37.762 --> 10:38.721
He asked me for a robe.

10:38.721 --> 10:40.306
Oh, come on, Ray!

10:40.306 --> 10:41.683
We're using him
for good stuff.

10:41.683 --> 10:43.476
What kind of kid
wants to wear a robe?

10:43.476 --> 10:45.353
And what kind of robe?
He won't say.

10:45.353 --> 10:47.605
Well, is it like
a silky Hugh Hefner robe,

10:47.605 --> 10:49.649
or like a fluffy
grandma robe?

10:49.649 --> 10:53.987
It is a gray, ankle‐length,
Turkish terry‐cloth boys' robe

10:53.987 --> 10:58.366
with side‐flaps
for superior breathability.

10:58.366 --> 11:00.243
Gah!

11:02.287 --> 11:04.664
Stay.

11:04.664 --> 11:07.000
[ Scoffs ]

11:07.000 --> 11:09.294
[ Gasps ] 21!

11:09.294 --> 11:10.461
"18."

11:10.461 --> 11:12.297
Yeah, well, I can't do math.
I'm far too excited.

11:12.297 --> 11:15.300
Dealer busts.
You are on a role, mister.

11:17.760 --> 11:19.262
Are you tired, darling?

11:19.262 --> 11:20.847
Have you had enough?

11:20.847 --> 11:21.764
Should we go home?

11:21.764 --> 11:23.600
"So you give up?"

11:23.600 --> 11:25.685
I do not.
You just seemed tired.

11:25.685 --> 11:28.646
S‐U‐D ‐‐ "Suddenly I have
a lot more energy."

11:28.646 --> 11:30.190
All right, fine.

11:30.190 --> 11:31.816
Where to next, then?

11:36.654 --> 11:39.324
"L'Erotica"?
I think not'ica.

11:39.324 --> 11:42.327
You want to go here
with your mother?

11:42.327 --> 11:45.330
L‐U‐C‐‐
"Luckily, she's not here."

11:47.665 --> 11:50.460
Yo, Dylan!

11:50.460 --> 11:52.879
You texted something
about an accident

11:52.879 --> 11:55.256
and asthma and a mean dog?

11:55.256 --> 11:57.175
Yeah, I wasn't sure
what would get you here.

11:57.175 --> 11:58.509
But now that you are ‐‐

11:58.509 --> 12:01.638
I don't believe what you said
about being happier now.

12:01.638 --> 12:03.681
I think you miss
being the Grim Leaper,

12:03.681 --> 12:07.393
and I'm gonna dunk on your face
till I bring him out.

12:07.393 --> 12:09.187
[ Grunts ]

12:14.901 --> 12:16.778
Good.

12:16.778 --> 12:18.613
Yes!

12:18.613 --> 12:20.448
Come on! Rub it in!

12:20.448 --> 12:21.908
Give me some trash talk.

12:21.908 --> 12:23.117
Here, here ‐‐
I'll help you.

12:23.117 --> 12:24.661
I'm gonna murder
your family,

12:24.661 --> 12:27.247
then eat them
'cause you're bad at sports.

12:27.247 --> 12:29.916
We done?
What is wrong with you?

12:29.916 --> 12:31.834
Look, where's the fire?

12:31.834 --> 12:33.836
Where's this Kenneth?

12:33.836 --> 12:35.171
That guy's gone.

12:35.171 --> 12:37.423
This guy's much happier.

12:37.423 --> 12:40.426
I don't miss my old life
at all.

12:40.426 --> 12:42.512
Then why is there a Corvette key
hanging around your neck?

12:42.512 --> 12:45.139
What?

12:45.139 --> 12:49.185
Okay.
Maybe I do miss <i>that.</i>

12:49.185 --> 12:50.478
A lot.

12:50.478 --> 12:52.146
Do you know
where it is now?
[ Scoffs ]

12:52.146 --> 12:54.899
I sold it
like 20 years ago.

12:54.899 --> 12:56.150
But when I drove past it
this morning,

12:56.150 --> 12:57.610
it was
in front of the owner's house.

12:57.610 --> 12:59.195
Let's go.

12:59.195 --> 13:01.155
Okay. Let's do it.

13:01.155 --> 13:06.911
It's just me and my man
going to a naked‐lady place.

13:06.911 --> 13:08.246
Ahh. No, hold on,
hold on, hold on.

13:08.246 --> 13:09.914
I can't ‐‐ I can't do it.
I can't do it.

13:09.914 --> 13:11.124
You win. You win.

13:11.124 --> 13:13.126
Please, just come home
with me.

13:13.126 --> 13:17.880
"Like everything,
it's always 'with you.'"

13:17.880 --> 13:19.257
I mean, that's ridiculous.

13:19.257 --> 13:20.633
You can do plenty
on your own.

13:20.633 --> 13:21.718
"Oh, really?

13:21.718 --> 13:24.262
Name one other person like me
who does."

13:24.262 --> 13:25.638
Oh, please.

13:25.638 --> 13:28.308
I can think of someone right off
the top of my head.

13:28.308 --> 13:30.226
"Look me in the eye
and tell me

13:30.226 --> 13:32.145
it's not Wheels from" ‐‐
Yeah, no.

13:32.145 --> 13:33.354
It's Wheels
from Burger King Kids' Club.

13:33.354 --> 13:36.190
Okay, fine.
Thank you, detective.

13:36.190 --> 13:37.317
"You want to help me"?

13:37.317 --> 13:40.069
Yes, yes.

13:40.069 --> 13:42.780
"Understand...

13:42.780 --> 13:46.367
you can't do
everything for me."

13:46.367 --> 13:48.786
I do understand, JJ.

13:48.786 --> 13:51.664
"If you did,
you'd leave me alone.

13:51.664 --> 13:54.959
Can you?"

13:54.959 --> 13:56.252
[ Voice breaking ]
I can.

13:58.379 --> 14:00.882
Good luck finding a wife
who's as good a mom as I am.

14:05.053 --> 14:07.972
♪♪

14:07.972 --> 14:10.516
I manipulated you, Dad.

14:10.516 --> 14:12.894
It was wrong.

14:12.894 --> 14:16.689
So, would you wear anything
under the robe?

14:16.689 --> 14:18.149
Forget the robe.

14:18.149 --> 14:19.859
I‐I used you.

14:19.859 --> 14:22.779
For something so small,

14:22.779 --> 14:24.447
so weird.
Why?

14:24.447 --> 14:26.908
I mean, we're always
on top of each other here.

14:26.908 --> 14:28.451
I share a room.

14:28.451 --> 14:31.204
The towels
are not large or clean.

14:31.204 --> 14:34.040
A robe would allow
a modest young man like me

14:34.040 --> 14:36.000
a modicum of privacy.

14:36.000 --> 14:37.293
Okay.

14:37.293 --> 14:38.419
I get that.

14:38.419 --> 14:40.505
It's a nice, small problem.

14:40.505 --> 14:42.799
I may want to run away
from the big ones sometimes,

14:42.799 --> 14:44.383
but that makes it
all the more satisfying

14:44.383 --> 14:47.345
when I can solve one
of the little ones.

14:47.345 --> 14:48.721
Is the robe
getting traction?

14:48.721 --> 14:50.056
Ooh, stop talking
before I decide

14:50.056 --> 14:51.432
this is
one of the bigger problems.

14:55.895 --> 14:57.438
Pretty girl.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.941
Wheelchair badass.

14:59.941 --> 15:01.442
A wheelchair badass!

15:01.442 --> 15:02.527
Ooh!

15:02.527 --> 15:04.237
JJ, I found future you.

15:04.237 --> 15:06.823
I found you.

15:06.823 --> 15:09.867
Oh, my God,
future JJ drives.

15:09.867 --> 15:10.910
No, come back!

15:10.910 --> 15:12.036
No, no!
No, hey!

15:15.623 --> 15:17.542
[ Engine starts ]

15:17.542 --> 15:19.293
[ Tires screech ]

15:25.883 --> 15:27.301
So this is it?

15:27.301 --> 15:29.220
[ Sighs ]
What happened to her?

15:29.220 --> 15:30.680
It's really dirty.

15:30.680 --> 15:32.682
I know. But...

15:32.682 --> 15:34.642
you should've seen us
back in the day ‐‐

15:34.642 --> 15:37.311
cruising,
blasting tunes,

15:37.311 --> 15:40.022
eating burgers
with no regards for calories.

15:40.022 --> 15:41.274
I bet the key still works.

15:41.274 --> 15:43.609
I bet you're right.

15:43.609 --> 15:45.653
[ Car door closes ]

15:45.653 --> 15:46.904
Maya: [ Chuckles ]

15:46.904 --> 15:49.323
Future JJ drives like me.

15:49.323 --> 15:52.118
♪♪

15:58.416 --> 15:59.458
Lee: Let's take a money bath,
right?

15:59.458 --> 16:01.586
Yeah.
Yea‐‐

16:01.586 --> 16:03.421
What?
What the hell?

16:03.421 --> 16:05.214
I told the other one
at the casino.

16:05.214 --> 16:07.425
I won that money
fair and square.

16:07.425 --> 16:10.636
I am not some Rain Man guy,
okay?

16:10.636 --> 16:11.721
Stay away, lady!

16:11.721 --> 16:12.763
I will use this!

16:12.763 --> 16:13.764
No, no need for that.

16:13.764 --> 16:15.141
Hello.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.601
I mean, look at you.

16:16.601 --> 16:17.977
You got everything.

16:17.977 --> 16:19.937
You got a cool car,
a girlfriend,

16:19.937 --> 16:21.814
a cute little gun thingy.

16:21.814 --> 16:23.566
Did she just
call my gun cute?

16:23.566 --> 16:25.026
It's not a gun.
It's a Taser.

16:25.026 --> 16:26.569
Well, she doesn't
need to know that.

16:26.569 --> 16:27.904
Please, yo‐you got to
come with me.

16:27.904 --> 16:29.030
You have to meet my son.

16:29.030 --> 16:30.156
He's got C. P.

16:30.156 --> 16:32.617
Oh, not
a special‐needs mom.

16:32.617 --> 16:34.452
It's really late
for one of you guys.

16:34.452 --> 16:35.703
No, no, but you got to
come with me.

16:35.703 --> 16:38.164
Please.
I mean you no harm.

16:38.164 --> 16:38.998
My name's Maya,
by the way.

16:38.998 --> 16:40.208
Hi, I'm ‐‐ whoa!

16:40.208 --> 16:41.626
Oh, God!
Oh, no!

16:41.626 --> 16:43.044
I am so sorry!

16:43.044 --> 16:44.962
My hand spasmed.

16:44.962 --> 16:46.672
[ Groaning ] It's okay.

16:46.672 --> 16:48.799
My JJ gets those, too.

16:48.799 --> 16:52.053
[ Engine starts ]

16:52.053 --> 16:54.096
♪ Right about now ♪

16:54.096 --> 16:55.514
♪ The funk soul brother ♪

16:55.514 --> 16:57.183
♪ Check it out now ♪

16:57.183 --> 16:58.726
♪ The funk soul brother ♪

16:58.726 --> 17:00.019
♪ Right about now ♪

17:00.019 --> 17:02.813
Whoo!
Let's do this!

17:02.813 --> 17:03.814
[ Tires screech ]

17:03.814 --> 17:05.358
This is very wrong.

17:05.358 --> 17:06.817
The only reason
why we're doing this

17:06.817 --> 17:08.819
is because
it's even more wrong

17:08.819 --> 17:11.739
to let Sarah J go this long
without a bath.

17:11.739 --> 17:12.740
Oh, I'm sorry.

17:12.740 --> 17:15.243
Dylan, meet Sarah J.

17:15.243 --> 17:18.329
Sarah J, meet a girl
who can't play D.

17:18.329 --> 17:21.457
Are you trash‐talking
about our game?

17:21.457 --> 17:23.542
Ah, something about
being in this car.

17:23.542 --> 17:25.044
Also...

17:25.044 --> 17:27.463
is it a game
if you never scored?

17:27.463 --> 17:29.298
Nice.

17:29.298 --> 17:31.592
See, this is a Kenneth
I can get behind.

17:31.592 --> 17:33.928
Hey, this is a Kenneth
Kenneth can get behind.

17:33.928 --> 17:36.639
As much as I like
my life now,

17:36.639 --> 17:40.560
it's good to Grim Leap
a little.

17:40.560 --> 17:41.727
Did you have a chant?

17:41.727 --> 17:43.437
A motto or something?

17:43.437 --> 17:44.897
A war cry?

17:44.897 --> 17:46.774
In fact, we did.

17:46.774 --> 17:48.943
Go team!

17:48.943 --> 17:50.611
Good.

17:50.611 --> 17:52.238
It's really good.

17:52.238 --> 17:53.239
[ Exhales softly ]

17:53.239 --> 17:54.865
[ Exhales softly ]

17:54.865 --> 17:56.826
This is nice.

17:56.826 --> 17:59.036
And those guys thought
it was weird.

17:59.036 --> 18:01.789
Mm, didn't say
it wasn't weird.

18:01.789 --> 18:04.250
You know, Ray,
sometimes I do have trouble

18:04.250 --> 18:06.794
talking about the big stuff,
but maybe from now on,

18:06.794 --> 18:08.129
if you want to,

18:08.129 --> 18:10.756
we can put on our robes
and get real.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.091
We can call it
"Robe Talk."

18:12.091 --> 18:13.968
Or it doesn't have a name.

18:13.968 --> 18:16.345
Thanks, Dad.

18:16.345 --> 18:18.806
Pretty sure this goes
without saying, but...

18:18.806 --> 18:20.808
further down the line,

18:20.808 --> 18:23.853
whatever JJ wants or needs,

18:23.853 --> 18:25.146
I'm on it.

18:25.146 --> 18:27.398
It does not go
without saying.

18:27.398 --> 18:30.985
Appreciate you saying it.

18:30.985 --> 18:32.737
You do have something
under it, right?

18:32.737 --> 18:35.781
♪♪

18:39.952 --> 18:42.246
JJ.
Oh, there you are.

18:42.246 --> 18:44.665
I'm sorry I left you,
sweetheart.

18:46.375 --> 18:48.502
"I'm sorry
I hurt your feelings."

18:48.502 --> 18:49.754
It's okay.

18:49.754 --> 18:50.838
We're here for a reason.

18:50.838 --> 18:52.381
This is Lee.

18:52.381 --> 18:54.008
I found him getting
into his fancy car

18:54.008 --> 18:55.718
with his lovely girlfriend.

18:55.718 --> 18:56.927
This is JJ.

18:56.927 --> 18:58.596
Hey.
[ Imitates explosion ]

18:58.596 --> 19:00.514
I thought he might
be able to help you.

19:00.514 --> 19:03.809
It's the least I could do
after I put 50,000 volts

19:03.809 --> 19:04.810
through your mom.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.020
Not all bad.

19:06.020 --> 19:07.938
Recharged my phone.
Great.

19:07.938 --> 19:09.065
Well, I'll let you two talk.

19:09.065 --> 19:10.733
I'll just be over there.

19:10.733 --> 19:12.068
Give us a second.

19:12.068 --> 19:14.779
So, man,
what do you want to know?

19:14.779 --> 19:17.698
Get as many girls on your lap
as possible.

19:17.698 --> 19:19.700
I love your laser...

19:19.700 --> 19:22.495
♪♪

19:30.378 --> 19:32.421
Take my number.

19:32.421 --> 19:33.631
And you know what?

19:33.631 --> 19:36.801
I'm actually really glad
your mom got us together.

19:36.801 --> 19:39.178
She's, uh, a good lady.

19:39.178 --> 19:41.389
Mine was, uh,

19:41.389 --> 19:43.391
every bit as, um...

19:43.391 --> 19:44.975
[ Clicks tongue ]

19:44.975 --> 19:47.228
"Let's call it"

19:47.228 --> 19:50.022
P‐A‐S ‐‐ "passionate."

19:50.022 --> 19:51.315
[ Both laugh ]

19:51.315 --> 19:54.485
You know, mine did
everything for me,

19:54.485 --> 19:55.820
and I let her,

19:55.820 --> 20:00.533
but it kind of kept me
from doing things for myself.

20:00.533 --> 20:03.327
I guess what
I'm trying to say is ‐‐

20:03.327 --> 20:06.414
you're gonna have to
make some space for yourself

20:06.414 --> 20:09.750
if you ever want to
live your life.

20:09.750 --> 20:11.127
You know?

20:14.046 --> 20:15.005
Thank you.

20:15.005 --> 20:16.465
I'm sorry I shot you.

20:16.465 --> 20:17.758
Ah.

20:17.758 --> 20:19.135
See you later, JJ.

20:23.556 --> 20:25.182
You happy?

20:25.182 --> 20:28.102
So, can I give you
what you need, or what?

20:34.150 --> 20:35.234
You think you got
what it takes?

20:35.234 --> 20:36.902
[ Raspy voice ] Oh, you woke
the dragon, little girl.

20:36.902 --> 20:38.028
Now he's hungry.

20:38.028 --> 20:39.280
You're going down.

20:39.280 --> 20:41.574
First one to reach
for the milk...

20:41.574 --> 20:43.117
Both: Loses.

20:43.117 --> 20:44.368
Ready.

20:44.368 --> 20:45.536
Set.

20:45.536 --> 20:47.329
Go!

20:52.209 --> 20:54.879
[ Coughs ]

20:54.879 --> 20:56.130
[ Coughs ]

20:56.130 --> 20:57.381
[ Strained ]
You finished yours?

20:57.381 --> 20:59.592
'Cause I could go
for another one.

20:59.592 --> 21:01.761
[ Hiccups ] The trash‐talking
is making it worse.

21:01.761 --> 21:03.095
Mommy!

21:03.095 --> 21:04.805
Going Zen.
Gonna meditate through it.

21:04.805 --> 21:06.599
Hummmm...

21:06.599 --> 21:07.892
...mmmaaaagh!

21:07.892 --> 21:09.560
Oh [bleep]

21:09.560 --> 21:11.270
Agh! Agh!

21:11.270 --> 21:13.147
There's nothing happening!

21:13.147 --> 21:14.440
Yeah!
[ Sobbing ]

21:14.440 --> 21:15.691
Yeah!

21:15.691 --> 21:19.111
Drink the milk!

21:19.111 --> 21:21.489
Some of us
are trying to luxuriate.

21:21.489 --> 21:22.740
[ Groans ]
